5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.0245f3a3-71ba-4318-8e1a-92f8a717b90b.prompt=Root object ID\: 5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.04d7cd1f-a89f-42f9-a049-b4abcb54d8f0.prompt=Enter a value for host 5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.0814f1d5-026a-4b43-8994-d5aac2902c6f.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.1fe5418d-c6b5-477c-ab4b-64b95faf8f25.description=
Search for VMWare objects of type propsType and their properties (propsPathset) from a root object (if any) specified by propsRootObj and propsRootObj. Retrieve each object's properties one at a time from an initial search query ala SQL Query operation. Please see VMWare Integration Guide for more details.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP
user - VMWare username
password - VMWare user's password
port - Port to connect on
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https)
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation?
propsType - VMWare properties type (Task, Datacenter, VirtualMachine, etc.) to filter on. Type of object results desired.
propsPathset - Property filter's pathset, comma-delimited (eg. name, info.name, runtime.host)
propsRootObjType - VMWare object type (eg. VirtualMachine, HostSystem, ComputeResource,ResourcePool,Alarm)
propsRootObj - VMWare object ID

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - there are no more results to retrieve.

Returns\:
numberOfResults - Number of results from the query remaining to be retrieved
returnResult - Query result item or operation result
5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.20a57ec0-8ef2-4bbe-819f-18a164842898.prompt=String to Append \: 5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.4eda2945-8ed5-411f-9279-854db915f29b.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
5e68f121-d93d-4df4-8cf6-19c96ca53cd7.506412c0-3ab3-4bc8-955a-40039d09e4e5.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
